        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>P<hi rend="sup">to</hi> Cabello</placeName> <date>24 January 1854</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr.</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">By <persName>Captain Wilkins</persName> of the Paer&#44; I wrote<lb/> you&#44; forwarding at the same time Nine Spanish dollars<lb/> and by the Venezuela&#44; <persName>Capt<hi rend="sup">n</hi> Wilson</persName>&#44; who arrived after<lb/>wards&#44; I received the Hebrew Grammar and Lexicon&#44;<lb/> as also your favor of the <date>24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date> last&#59; I now beg<lb/> to remind you of the two copies of the new translation of<lb/> the Bible&#44; and one copy of the form of prayers&#44; as speci<lb/>fied on the prospectus forwarded by letter of the <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of De<lb/>cember 1852</date>&#44; as I observe in the last numbers of the<lb/> Occident&#44; that they are near being issued&#44; if not issued<lb/> already.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed I beg to hand you a list of some works<lb/> etc. which I would wish very much to possess&#44; especial<lb/>ly for the use of my children&#44; as my family will shortly<lb/> come to reside in this place&#44; where educational works<lb/> are scarce to be had&#44; of inferior utility and at exorbi<lb/>tant prices. I thought you would forgive the liberty<lb/> I take in begging the favor of you to procure them for<lb/> me&#44; as I felt assured of your willingness to be of service<lb/> to a fellow&#45;creature&#44; and perform a good act&#59; but as I<lb/> am also very far from wishing&#44; that you should any<lb/> <hi rend="underline">ways</hi></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>wise incommode yourself&#44; I beg that&#44; if the purchase of<lb/> them should by any means inconvenience you&#44; you should<lb/> inform me&#44; what may be the cost of the books etc. re<lb/>quired&#44; so as to enable me to remit the required funds.<lb/> I leave the choice of the books as far as they are educaton<lb/>al&#44; and not specified to your superior <sic>judgement</sic></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Believe me Dear Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Yours sincerely</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">A Myerston</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>please let me know the name of the street<lb/> in which you reside.</p>
			<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
			<p><placeName><hi rend="underline">371 Walnut</hi></placeName></p>
          
        </body>
